MechFight is a role-playing game. You can explore a world, buy or find 
items and fight against robots and aliens. During the game you are asked
to fulfil some tasks.




                  How to install MechFight on a harddisk
                  ======================================

You can do this simply by dragging the GAME- AND(!) the
EDITOR-drawer-icons from the disk to your harddisk. Please make sure
that the EDITOR and the GAME subdirectories are in the same directory
of your harddisk.


                            Starting MechFight
                            ==================

                          Booting from the disk
                          ---------------------

Turn on your computer or use Ctrl-Amiga-Amiga to reboot. When the
workbench disk picture appears, insert the MechFight disk.
Wait for the workbench screen to appear.

NOTE: You can also start MechFight without booting from the disk. In this
case, it will use the standard topaz font unless you have the flow-font in
your fonts:-directory.


      **************************************************************
      ** NOTE:                                                    **
      ** The "MechFight"-disk MUST NOT BE WRITE-PROTECTED!!!      **
      ** (Otherwise MF will get stuck when it tries to save levels**
      ** on the disk).                                            **
      **************************************************************

Double-click on the disk-icon. Then double-click on the GAME-icon.
Wait for the MF-icon to appear and double-click on it.
(If you do not want to see the title pictures every time you start MF,
you must press the left mouse button immediately after having
double-clicked on the icon. You mustn't release it until the MechFight-
display appears on the screen.)

Click once on the MF-screen to activate it.

Enter your name. You only have to do this once.

You start in Beta-X, a space station in the orbit of BAHRAN, a planet
with a rocky underground and a thin atmosphere.
You do not have any items at first. Explore the station, earn some money,
buy weapons and shields and try to find persons who give you some tasks.



                               The display
                               ===========

There are three main elements in the display: the textwindow, the 
scrollwindow and the gadgets.

Every message appears in the textwindow. Sometimes you are told something
about the room you are in or you are told whether you have hit an enemy or
he has hit you.

In the SCROLLWINDOW, you see a small part of the landscape (the
"PlayMap"). If you move your robot, this visible part of the landscape
will scroll in the appropriate direction.

                               The GADGETS:
                               ------------

There are four arrow-gadgets to the right of the scroll window. Clicking
with the mouse on them will cause your robot to move in the indicated
direction. The gadget in the middle of the four arrows is for using
your weapon. (Lasers, machine guns, grenades, bombs and short-range
weapons).
The lower three gadgets are labelled WEAPONS, COM and STATUS.
In this version, WEAPONS and COM do not cause any useful actions.
Clicking on the STATUS-gadget will bring up a status-message of the
form:

STATUS:
ENERGY: Your energy, 0 means you are destroyed. SST: Your
shooting-strength, depends on the type/level of your long-range-weapon.
HST: Your hit-strength, depends on the type/level of your short-range-
weapon. AC: Armor-Class. Standard level is 200. The lower the level the
better for you. AC=0 would mean you can't be hit at all. AC depends
on the type/level of your shield.
CREDITS: The amount of money you are carrying. DEX: Dexterity.
Standard value is 10. A lower value means you can hit (short-range-wp)
in shorter intervals.
SRWP: Your current short-range-weapon
LRWP: Your current long-range-weapon
SHLD: Your current shield.

A typical example of a STATUS-message:

STATUS:
ENERGY: 3500  SST: 80  HST: 60  AC: 170
CREDITS: 1578 DEX: 10
SRWP: Striker
LRWP: ML Laser
SHLD: Std Shield

                                 The menu
                                 ========

If you click on the right mouse button once, a menu will appear under the
mouse cursor. It looks like this:

                               /---------\
                               | Menu:   |
                               | Actions |
                               | Game    |
                               | Cancel  |
                               \---------/


                           The Actions submenu
                           -------------------
looks like this:

                              /-----------\
                              | Actions:  |
                              | Inventory |
                              | Take      |
                              | Drop      |
                              | SRWeapon  |
                              | LRWeapon  |
                              | Shield    |
                              | Cancel    |
                              \-----------/

Inventory: Displays all your eight items in the form
           Nr. ITEMNAME TYPE#AMOUNT
           3   E Bit       E#03
Take     : Takes an item at the current position if there is any.
           (Otherwise you are told "There is nothing")
           Example: You find: ML Laser. Do you want to take it (y/n) ?
           --> Type 'y' or 'n' on the keyboard.
           You can use take everywhere (not only when you stand on
           containers, blue boxes or a destroyed robot.)
           There may seem to be nothing in a room, but using "Take" might
           reveal some hidden items.
Drop     : By this command you can drop an item. Select this item with
           the mouse: Click on it in the inventory list which will be
           displayed.
SRWeapon : Select your short-range-weapon with the mouse by clicking
           on it in the displayed list.
   >>>              A short-range-weapon is of the TYPE 'R'        <<<
LRWeapon : Select your long-range-weapon in the same way.
    >>>              A long-range-weapon is of the TYPES 'F'-'L'   <<<
               (G=grenade, K=bomb, L=laser or machine gun)
Shield   : Select your shield.
         >>>              A shield is of the TYPE 'S'        <<<

                            Other item-types:
                            =================

'E': Energy-item. Collect it and you'll get more energy.
'C': ID-Card.


                                 Weapons
                                 =======

LASERS just fire laser bolts.
GRENADES are fired at a maximum distance of 5 fields. They explode and
randomly hit nearby objects (robots etc.).
BOMBS are laid on the field in front of you. A timer will start and
after some while they'll explode. They can destroy some walls or rocks,
depending on the level of the BOMB. They also damage robots, aliens or
even yourself if you don't take care and get away quickly.

NOTE: A bomb of level 5 (i.e. when equipped, your SST is 5) corresponds
to a laser of level 50. With grenades it is the same.



                             The Game submenu
                             ----------------

                                /--------\
                                | Game:  |
                                | Quit   |
                                | Debug  |
                                | Coords |
                                | Cancel |
                                \--------/

Quit     : Quit the game. You can choose whether you want to save the
           current status or not.
Debug    : Not for you. (Enter a number ranging from 0 to 200. 0=player)
Coords   : Displays the coordinates of the robot.



