Arrow-
keys      : Move.

t         : Take.
i         : Inventory.



                       Messages and special fields
                       ===========================

If you step on certain fields (which sometimes don't seem to be special
at all), messages will appear - sometimes descriptions of places,
sometimes computers requesting you to enter a password, sometimes an
information.
There are fields that teleport you to another location or even to another
level. Some fields cause a door to open or to close, a hostile robot to
appear etc. There are also fields which show pictures or check if
you have a special item (e.g. an ID-Card).
It may be that you even don't notice you have stepped on such a field.
There are fields which will start a timer and after a short while a
bomb will explode, a door will open, a message will appear or something
else may happen.



                                  Saving
                                  ======

The current level is saved automatically if you enter a new one.
(by teleporting). If you return to the old level, all monsters you have
killed aren't there any more.
If you want to quit the game, you are asked whether you want to save.
If not, the next time you play MF you will start at the point where
you were when you saved the last time. BUT THE LEVELS WILL HAVE BEEN
SAVED IN SPITE OF THIS, EXCEPT FOR THE LAST LEVEL. (This is because
every level is saved when you enter a new one).
If you are playing MF for the first time and don't save when exiting,
MF will believe you are a new player when you restart it, although the
levels may have been changed by your last game.

TO RESET ALL, FOLLOW THE INSTRUCTIONS AT "Beginning a new game".

If you type 'y' when exiting the game, a file called 'Player.save' will
be saved to disk. It contains information about your name, the current
level, your coordinates, the 8 items you are carrying, your srwp,lrwp and
shld, your energy,ac,sst,hst,dex and credits.
This file will automatically be loaded the next time you play MF.

Normally, you should save every time you quit MF, because otherwise you
might get into serious trouble. (An item isn't there any more and it
isn't in your inventory either - so if it was an important one, you can't
continue).

Another possibility is to quit and re-enter the game every time you enter
a new level. When you are killed, you can continue from the old position,
because the current level is only saved when you quit.




                           Beginning a new game
                           ====================

If you have died or are stuck, you might want to begin a new game. You
can do this by double-clicking on the NEW_GAME - icon which should be
in the GAME - drawer. All necessary files will be recopied from
the EDITOR-drawer to the GAME-drawer. (files with the endings .it,.objs,
.pm,.texts,.texts.l). The Player.save - file will be deleted.
If you restart MF now, you will be asked for your name and will start
in the space station. (like it was when you first played MF)
